x4freetext: Experiment was conducted at Triangle
Universities Nuclear Laboratory using the 10 MV FN
Tandem accelerator facility.
The target consisted of a thin
enriched 10B layer of 100 mu-g/cm2 nominal thickness,
deposited on a thin carbon foil ( 40 mu-g/cm2).
An array of silicon surface barrier detectors
was used to detect the outgoing alpha particles. Each
detector was placed at a specific angle at a distance
of 16 cm from the target, subtending a solid angle of
approx. 4.5E-4 sr.
Systematic uncertainty
Compiled by S.H.
